======================================================================
T=10 GAP ANALYSIS (H=21 IMPOSSIBILITY)
======================================================================

--- CUBIC EXCLUSION LEMMA ---
CLAIM: alpha_3 >= 1 implies T >= 13
PROOF:
  alpha_3 >= 1: exists 3 mutually vertex-disjoint odd cycles
  => alpha_1 >= 3 (at least these 3 cycles exist)
  => alpha_2 >= C(3,2) = 3 (each pair of the 3 cycles is disjoint)
  => T = a1 + 2*a2 + 4*a3 + ... >= 3 + 6 + 4 = 13
  Since T=10 < 13, we conclude alpha_3 = 0 for any T=10 tournament.
  Similarly alpha_k = 0 for all k >= 3.

  GENERALIZATION: alpha_k >= 1 implies:
  alpha_2 >= 1 => T >= (3^2-1)/2 = 4
  alpha_3 >= 1 => T >= (3^3-1)/2 = 13
  alpha_4 >= 1 => T >= (3^4-1)/2 = 40
  alpha_5 >= 1 => T >= (3^5-1)/2 = 121
  alpha_6 >= 1 => T >= (3^6-1)/2 = 364
  alpha_7 >= 1 => T >= (3^7-1)/2 = 1093

  BEAUTIFUL: the bound is T >= (3^k - 1)/2!
  k=1: T >= 1 (trivial)
  k=2: T >= 4 (one disjoint pair)
  k=3: T >= 13 (blocks T=10!)
  k=4: T >= 40
  The generating function: sum C(k,j)*2^{j-1} = (3^k-1)/2
  This is (I(K_k, 2) - 1) / 2 where K_k is the empty graph on k vertices!

--- ACHIEVABLE T-SPECTRUM ---

